# ERC1271

ERC1271 is a standard interface for smart contracts to validate signatures. It enables contracts to implement custom signature verification logic, extending signature capabilities beyond Externally Owned Accounts (EOAs). The standard defines an `isValidSignature` function that takes a message hash and a signature, returning a specific magic value (`0x1626ba7e`) if the signature is valid. This allows for complex signature schemes like multi-sig wallets, smart contract wallets, and delegated signing. ERC1271 is crucial for account abstraction, decentralized exchanges with off-chain orders, and Sign-In With Ethereum (SIWE) implementations.

```solidity
interface IERC1271 {
    function isValidSignature(bytes32 hash, bytes memory signature) external view returns (bytes4 magicValue);
}
```
